Message: Social media is already filling up with misinformation about a Covid-19 vaccine, months or years before one even exists. "The anti-vaxxers have been practicing for this," writes Kevin Roose. "And I’m worried that they will be unusually effective."
We’ve been warning about this for 6 years...
Anti-Vaxx activists are already railing against a possible Covid-19 vaccine. Conspiracies flood internet.

To recover from this pandemic, we need to mobilize a pro-vaccine movement that is as devoted, as internet-savvy and as compelling as the anti-vaccine movement is for its adherents. We need to do it quickly, with all the creativity and urgency of the scientists who are developing the vaccine itself. Millions of lives and trillions of dollars in economic activity may depend not just on producing a vaccine, but on persuading people to accept it.
Anti-vaxxers have gotten so effective at pushing misinformation that scientists are now concerned when a Covid-19 vaccine does come out many will simply refuse to take it.
Get ready for the antivaxers and pray we actually do develop a vaccine.
hopefully the moronic anti-vaxxers will die off soon.
